06/03/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prosecutors in the town of Split have filed charges against four Croatian citizens for war crimes committed during the 1991-1995 conflict, local media reported on Saturday (March 5th).
The four former military police officers allegedly participated in the torture and inhuman treatment of Serbian prisoners at the Kuline military prison in Sibenik in 1992.
(HRT, Beta, B92 - 05/03/11)
